  "notes": "Skeleton. Old East Slavic / Old Russian (c. 10th-14th c.), common ancestor of Russian, Ukrainian and Belarusian. Early Cyrillic including the yers ъ/ь and yat ѣ; the reduced yers are given their strong-position values and jer weakening/loss is unencoded. Church Slavonic adstrate.",
